Increase stackrox namespace storage quota to unblock RHACS Central upgrade

Description:
During the RHACS upgrade, the Central custom resource is unable to create the central-db-backup PVC because the current stackrox namespace storage quota is exceeded. As a result, the upgrade is stuck in a partial state, with some components still showing version 4.7.x. Based on Red Hat guidance, increasing the namespace storage/resource quota is the required next step to allow the operator to continue reconciliation and complete the Central database migration and upgrade successfully.
